  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marketing Intern",
  "description": "<h3>Marketing Internship Opportunity</h3><p><strong>Duration</strong>: 3 - 6 months</p><p><strong>Location</strong>: Hybrid</p><p><strong>Availability</strong>: Open to diploma students and undergraduates</p><p>Are you a storyteller at heart with a creative eye for design? Join our small but dynamic marketing team! This isn't your typical \"coffee-run\" internship. You’ll be right in the thick of it—brainstorming campaigns, filming content, and helping us build a vibrant community. If you are proactive, love lifestyle branding, and aren’t afraid to get your hands dirty, we want to hear from you.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities:</h3><ul><li><strong>Graphic Design & Visuals:</strong> Design eye-catching assets, including stickers, social media graphics, and marketing materials that resonate with our audience.</li><li><strong>Creative Content Creation:</strong> Collaborate with the team to conceptualize, script, and film short-form videos (TikTok/Reels style) and static content for cross-channel campaigns.</li><li><strong>Community & Events</strong>: Comfortable with engaging users face-to-face and helping to execute on-ground activations.</li><li><strong>Brand Voice:</strong> Ensure all written copy and visual designs align with our \"fun and relatable\" brand personality.</li></ul><h3>You’ll be a great fit if you are:</h3><ul><li>Undergraduate student or diploma holder in Marketing/Communications, Graphic Design, Media, or related fields.</li><li>You move fast and aren’t afraid to get your hands dirty — whether it’s writing copy or filming a video.</li><li>A highly motivated team player who enjoy working in a collaborative environment but is also comfortable taking initiative and working independently.</li><li>Have a flair for writing and can articulate ideas clearly in a tone that’s fun and relatable.</li><li>Can juggle multiple tasks, meet deadlines, and thrive in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Bonus if you have skills in Motion Graphics, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Premiere Pro or other similar softwares. Extra bonus if you love cycling!</li></ul><p>Apply now with your resume and portfolio with all relevant works to judith@anywheel.sg</p>",
